article.headline: Drake 76, UC Irvine 73
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Klayton Korver had 20 points and seven rebounds, and Drake overcame an 18-point deficit in the second half, beating the the UC-Irvine 76-73. Ajay Calvin added 16 points and nine rebounds, and Nick Grant scored 14 for Drake (6-2) which went on a 19-4 run late in the second half to secure a win. The 18 point second-half comeback was one of the largest in Drake's history. The Bulldogs looked out of sync in the first half, missing several open layups, but rallied behind Korver's three-point shooting in the second half. The Bulldogs' victory came on a night when fans were charged only $1 for admission. UC-Irvine (3-6) was led by Adam Templeton, who had 19 points and six rebounds, including 5-9 three-pointers. Michael Hunter also added 13 points and five rebounds for the Anteaters.
